                <head>215. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The United States and the United Kingdom concluded an agreement on grain imports
                    by an exchange of notes between Ambassador <persName>David K.E. Bruce</persName>
                    and the Earl of Dundee, British Minister of State for Foreign Affairs, in London
                    on April 15, 1964. The agreement entered into force on the same date. For text,
                    see 15 <gloss target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> 541; TIAS 5581. For Special
                    Representative <persName corresp="#p_HCAJ1">Herter</persName>’s statement of
                    April 16 announcing the agreement, see Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                        >Bulletin</hi>, May 4, 1964, pages 703–704. Additional documentation on the
                    negotiations leading to this agreement is in Department of State, Central Files,
                    INCO–GRAINS 17 <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>-US.</p>
            </div>
